T*
(Link: https://geohot.github.io//blog/jekyll/update/2026/05/24/the-eternal-sloptember.html) Tj
T*
(I?m calling it now, the adoption of AI agents into software development will be one of the most) Tj
T*
(costly mistakes in the field?s history. Agents cannot program, and it?s taking longer and) Tj
T*
(longer to realize that they can?t. They are a highly sophisticated statistical model designed) Tj
T*
(to mimic the distribution of programming. The output is broken, but in a way that?s getting) Tj
T*
(harder and harder to detect. Which is exactly what you?d expect from an increasingly accurate) Tj
T*
(statistical model. At first, I rejected this. I bought into the Twitter explanation of status) Tj
T*
(anxiety. I define some of my self worth by my programming abilities, so wouldn?t it make sense) Tj
T*
(to get defensive around that loss? Deny the models can code for as long as I could to preserve) Tj
T*
(my ego? I mean, it?s very clear they can solve math problems I couldn?t hope to solve if I) Tj
